two bones over the eyes, with the hair and flesh upon them:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(IF, Msb, K:) or the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "eyebrow;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "hair growing on either of those bones:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(AZ, K:) so called because it precludes the rays of the sun from the eye: (TA:) of the masc. gender: (Lh TA:) pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HawaAjibu", "text_ar": "حَوَاجِبُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (S Msb, K.) One says,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_in~ahu lamuzaj~aju", "text_ar": "اـِنَّهُ لَمُزَجَّجُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlHaAjibi", "text_ar": "الحَاجِبِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Verily he has the eyebrow made narrow and long, by the removal of redundant hairs;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "made narrow and long and arched; or lengthened with antimony"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (Lh, TA.) ―         -b3-  [Hence, as being likened thereto,] (assumed tropical:)  The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "piece of wood that is over the lintel of a door-frame."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Az, TA.) [See"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EatabapN", "text_ar": "عَتَبَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".] ―         -b4-  (tropical:)  The edge, (A,) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "side,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K,) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "upper limb of the disk, that appears when it begins to rise,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, TA,) or the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "first part that appears,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Mgh,) of the sun, (T, A, Mgh, K,) and of the moon: (T, TA:) likened to the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HAjb", "text_ar": "حاجب"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A, Mgh) of the face (Mgh) of a man: (A:) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HawaAjbu Al$~amos", "text_ar": "حَوَاجبُ الشَّمْس"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the sides of the sun."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S.) You say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "badaA HaAjibu", "text_ar": "بَدَا حَاجِبُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Al$~amos", "text_ar": "الشَّمْس"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (T, A, TA,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alqamari", "text_ar": "القَمَرِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (T, TA,) (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The upper limb of the disk,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, TA,) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the edge,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of the sun appeared,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, A, TA,) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of the moon."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, TA.) ―         -b5-  (assumed tropical:)  The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "edge"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or anything. (K.) A woman said to a man who was eating of the middle of a round cake of bread,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kulo mino HawaAjibihaA", "text_ar": "كُلْ مِنْ حَوَاجِبِهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Eat of its edges,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(As, TA,) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "its sides."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A.) ―         -b6-  (assumed tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The beginning"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of the dawn.] You say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laAHato", "text_ar": "لَاحَتْ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HawaAjibu AlS~uboHi", "text_ar": "حَوَاجِبُ الصُّبْحِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The beginnings of the dawn appeared."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A, TA.)"}], "source_refs": ["TA", "Msb", "S", "K", "IF", "AZ", "A", "T", "Mgh", "As"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}